    <chapter>
      
        <title>Private Key Protection</title>
        <para>This section defines the algorithms used to protect private keys during transit between key generation to key upload.
          PBKDF2 (defined in <xref linkend="keyTable"/>) is used to derive the encryption key from
          a password, and AES-CBC (defined in <xref linkend="symTable"/>) is used to wrap
          the private key material in PKCS#12 format (RFC 7292).</para>
        <table xml:id="certTable">
          <title>Private Key Protection Algorithms</title>
          <tgroup cols="3">
            <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="2*"/>
            <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="1*"/>
            <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="2*"/>
            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry><para>Algorithm</para></entry>
                <entry><para>Reference</para></entry>
                <entry><para>Capability</para></entry>
              </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody valign="top">
              <row>
                <entry><para>PBKDF2 + AES-CBC</para></entry>
                <entry><para>RFC 8018</para></entry>
                <entry><para>PasswordBasedEncryptionAlgorithms</para></entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </table>
      <para>Note that this covers PKCS#12
          key transport; device-internal at-rest key storage may use stronger direct encryption
          as required by the applicable profile specification.</para>
  </chapter>
